    Frequently Asked Questions

    What is the median home price in Irvine?
    Homes for sale in Irvine have a median listing price of $950K. Some of these homes are Hot Homes, meaning they're likely to sell quickly.
    How long do homes stay on the market in Irvine?
    Most homes for sale in Irvine stay on the market for 59 days and receive 3 offers. In the past month, 744 homes have been sold in Irvine. The median price per square foot in Irvine has increased by 0.42% over the past year.
    What are some of the most popular neighborhoods in Irvine?
    Popular neighborhoods include Baker Ranch, Shady Canyon, North Tustin, Newport Beach, Costa Mesa, Orchard Hills, Tustin Ranch, Turtle Ridge, Turtle Rock, Lake Forest, Quail Hill, Tustin, Woodbridge, Laguna Woods Village, and Orange County Great Park.
    How often does Redfin update their new listings?
    Redfin is refreshed with the  newest listings in Irvine every 15 minutes.
